Organization Name: MHMR OF TARRANT COUNTY | ARLINGTON CLINIC FOR YOUTH AND ADULTS | I-CARE CALL CENTER
Description: Provides a central site to determine eligibility for 24-hour crisis evaluation and support. Also, provides a crisis respite unit, mobile response team, case management /counseling, supported housing, inpatient treatment for adults, adolescents and children.

Organization Name: MHMR OF TARRANT COUNTY | MAIN OFFICE | I-CARE CALL CENTER
Description: Provides a central site to determine eligibility for 24-hour crisis evaluation and support. Also, provides a crisis respite unit, mobile response team, case management /counseling, supported housing, inpatient treatment for adults, adolescents and children.

The mission of The Jordan Elizabeth Harris Foundation (JEHF) is to prevent suicide, eliminate stigma, and provide hope to people struggling with depression. Since 2014, The JEHF has been providing non-clinical evidence-based suicide prevention training and education to children, teens, and adults in Tarrant County. The Foundation provides programs to schools, faith communities and workplaces in North Texas, and creates custom solutions to meet the diverse needs of communities and people of different backgrounds and experiences. In addition to these aspects, The Foundation funds research, encourages awareness and connects people in crisis with direct support across the region.
